Title: Test Scenarios for Displaying Login Button to Guest Users in Account Section

Test Scenarios:

A. Positive Test Cases
  1. Verify that the Login button is visible in the account section when accessed by a guest user.
  2. Verify that the Login button is enabled and clickable for guest users.
  3. Verify that clicking the Login button as a guest user navigates to the login page.
  4. Verify that the Login button displays the correct label/text as per design specifications.

B. Negative Test Cases
  5. Verify that the Login button is not visible in the account section when accessed by a logged-in (authenticated) user.
  6. Verify that the Login button is not visible if the account section fails to load due to a backend error.
  7. Verify that the Login button is not visible for users with a corrupted or invalid session.
  8. Verify that the Login button is not visible for users with restricted access (e.g., banned or blocked users, if applicable).

C. Boundary Test Cases
  9. Verify the visibility and accessibility of the Login button at the minimum supported screen resolution.
  10. Verify the visibility and accessibility of the Login button at the maximum supported screen resolution.
  11. Verify the Login button’s placement and visibility when the account section contains the maximum number of UI elements or widgets.
  12. Verify the Login button’s visibility and functionality on different device types (desktop, tablet, mobile).

D. Non-Functional Test Cases
  13. Verify that the Login button loads within 2 seconds after the account section is rendered.
  14. Verify that the Login button is accessible via keyboard navigation (tab order).
  15. Verify that the Login button is properly announced by screen readers for accessibility compliance.
  16. Verify that the Login button label is correctly localized in all supported languages.
  17. Verify that the Login button is visible and functional across major browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge).
  18. Verify that the Login button does not expose any sensitive information or security vulnerabilities to guest users.
  19. Verify the usability of the Login button (e.g., size, color contrast, and placement meet UI/UX guidelines).

Additional Details:
  - User Story Reference: SCRUM-5
  - Priority: High
  - Notes: Ensure the Login button is only visible to guest users and not to authenticated users. All scenarios should be validated against UI/UX and accessibility standards. Update scenarios if acceptance criteria are refined.

----------

Test Case ID: TC001
Test Case Title: Verify Login button is visible in the account section for guest users
Preconditions: User is not logged in (guest session). Account section is accessible.
Test Steps:
1. Navigate to the application’s home page.
2. Access the account section as a guest user.
Expected Result: The Login button is visible in the account section.
Priority: High
Dependencies: User authentication system, Account section UI

Test Case ID: TC002
Test Case Title: Verify Login button is enabled and clickable for guest users
Preconditions: User is not logged in (guest session). Account section is accessible.
Test Steps:
1. Navigate to the application’s home page.
2. Access the account section as a guest user.
3. Observe the Login button.
4. Attempt to click the Login button.
Expected Result: The Login button is enabled and can be clicked.
Priority: High
Dependencies: User authentication system, Account section UI

Test Case ID: TC003
Test Case Title: Verify navigation to login page when Login button is clicked by guest user
Preconditions: User is not logged in (guest session). Account section is accessible.
Test Steps:
1. Navigate to the application’s home page.
2. Access the account section as a guest user.
3. Click the Login button.
Expected Result: User is redirected to the login page.
Priority: High
Dependencies: Login page, Navigation system

Test Case ID: TC004
Test Case Title: Verify Login button displays correct label/text as per design
Preconditions: User is not logged in (guest session). Account section is accessible.
Test Steps:
1. Navigate to the application’s home page.
2. Access the account section as a guest user.
