Test Case ID: TC005
Test Case Title: Verify Login button is not visible for authenticated users
Preconditions: User is logged in (authenticated session). Account section is accessible.
Test Steps:
1. Log in with valid user credentials.
2. Access the account section.
Expected Result: The Login button is not visible in the account section.
Priority: High
Dependencies: User authentication system

Test Case ID: TC006
Test Case Title: Verify Login button is not visible if account section fails to load due to backend error
Preconditions: Simulate backend error causing account section to fail loading.
Test Steps:
1. Trigger a backend error (e.g., disconnect backend service).
2. Navigate to the application’s home page.
3. Access the account section.
Expected Result: The Login button is not visible (account section does not load).
Priority: Medium
Dependencies: Backend service, Error handling

Test Case ID: TC007
Test Case Title: Verify Login button is not visible for users with corrupted or invalid session
Preconditions: User session is corrupted or invalid.
Test Steps:
1. Corrupt or invalidate the user session (e.g., manipulate session cookie).
2. Navigate to the application’s home page.
3. Access the account section.
Expected Result: The Login button is not visible.
Priority: Medium
Dependencies: Session management system

Test Case ID: TC008
